content:
We've provided out-of-the-box components for Insurance Experience sites, but you'll probably want to brand them with your logos, icons, colors, and fonts. You can customize the look and feel of the components, change the placement of elements on cards, add or remove data on cards, create new data sources, and build new components using FlexCards.

The process for configuring most site components is a bit complicated, but you'll get the hang of it. To customize FlexCard-based components, follow these steps:

Clone a Component's FlexCard
Manage the Data Source for an Experience Component
Customize a Component
Replace a Customized LWC on an Experience Component
Add Customized Components to the Site

Some components are not built using FlexCards and require a different process. You can also use Vlocity Cards designer to customize classic card-based components.

If you need to replace an out-of-box component with your extended one, follow the same process as for FlexCard components. Use the same process to customize non-FlexCard based components as well.
title: Customizing Insurance Digital Experience Site Components
